articles.headline: Sources: Jaguars trade running back Tank Bigsby to Eagles
articles.description: The Jacksonville Jaguars are trading running back Tank Bigsby, who had five carries for 12 yards Sunday in a win over the Carolina Panthers, to the Philadelphia Eagles in exchange for 2026 fifth- and sixth-round picks, sources told ESPN's Adam Schefter.

articles.description: The Eagles added some running back depth behind Saquon Barkley, but did they give up too much for Bigsby? We sized up the deal from both sides.

articles.headline: Bears letter to fans reiterates new stadium will be built in suburbs
articles.description: The Chicago Bears all but slammed the door on building an enclosed stadium in the city, with team president Kevin Warren writing in a letter to fans Monday that the team's "future home" is in suburban Arlington Heights.
